https://3v4l.org/qd6DQ

Note, the format is `PeriodDurationDesignator`. `P###(D/M/Y/W)` for day/month/year/week (`P10D` for 10 day period). For time, add a `T`: `PT###(H/M/S)` or `PT10S` for a 10 second period.


  [1]: https://www.php.net/manual/en/dateinterval.construct.php

You can use the Modify method of DateTime to add minutes. If the result is greater than a date of the same day 19:00, then the next day is taken and the rest is added.

    $minutesAdd = 45;
    $strDate = &quot;2019-10-10 18:25:00&quot;;
    
    $dateTime = date_create($strDate)
